{# 
    Input Prompt (<isindex>)
    ===========================================================================

    Defines a single-line input field for entering text.

    Variables:
    - `isindex_prompt`: The prompt message displayed before the input field.
      Defaults to "Enter search term:".
    - `isindex_action`: The URL to which the form data will be submitted.
      Defaults to "#".

    Notes:
    - The <isindex> element is deprecated in HTML5 and should not be used.
      Consider using <input> elements within a <form> instead.
    - The `| e` filter is used to escape any special characters in the
      variables to prevent XSS attacks.

    Links:
    - https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/isindex
    - https://www.w3schools.com/tags/tag_isindex.asp

#}

<isindex
    prompt="{{ isindex_prompt | default('Enter search term:') | e }}"
    action="{{ isindex_action | default('#') | e }}"
>
